info.description:
ViffBench is a set of scripts that makes it easy to write, execute, and
visulize benchmarks of VIFF protocols. Features include

* Benchmarking using arbitrary VIFF revisions.

* Based on ssh and thus benefits from key agents like ssh-agent.

* Benchmarking of distributed VIFF protocols as well as local VIFF code.

* Automatically stores benchmark results in central database.

* Stores benchmark results for every single run, e.g. no info is lost.
